long_desc.thetext:
See the attached config.log and build.log for details about the undefined reference error.
I found several (possible) issue in configure.ac:
- Line 687: I had to adjust some library paths which might be related to my dist (Gentoo Linux). Anyways, "libcom_err" in the AFS lib was renamed to "libafscom_err", see http://git.openafs.org/?p=openafs.git;a=commit;h=352c3e366c2e0a8de4550547192276e62afd2cc1.
- Line 734: The AM_CONDITIONAL runs [test "$HAVE_AFSKRB" = "1"] to define or undefined USE_AFSKRB. This cannot work since $HAVE_AFSKRB is never defined. The AC_DEFINE(HAVE_AFSKRB ...) statements above only add the appropriate defines to the config.h and does not define any shell vars. You can find a workaround in the patch attached that is using "grep HAVE_AFSKRB confdefs.h" - I'm not proud but my AC knowledge is limited and this seems to work.
Please find attached a patch that fixes those issues for me.
